The paper discusses a fundamental database operator, set similarity join, and presents a new randomized algorithm that significantly improves on existing methods. The paper also makes use of recent theoretical advances in high-dimensional sketching and indexing. Based on this information, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DB (Databases), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses theoretical and empirical results, which suggest that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
